  "texts": [
    "Figure 5 shows the results of the LLM evaluation of insightfulness on all public databases.",
    "Overall, all methods based on our approach perform better than baselines, with HLI clearly at the top and Quick performing the worst.",
    "Following the correctness definition from Section 2.2.2, the truth value of each insight is the mean of the truth value of its claims scoring 1 when true and 0 when false.",
    "Some claims that contain multiple subclaims have been evaluated as a b, where b is the number of subclaims and a, the number of correct ones.",
    "4 We consider the score of each method to be the mean correctness of the evaluated insights from that method."
  ],
